@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Developer API";
}

<h1 class="mb-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
<p class="lead">Integrate FluxDoc's powerful document manipulation and intelligence capabilities directly into your applications.</p>

<div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
    <strong>"Dev Dave" persona focus:</strong> Reliable RESTful API with API Keys and rate limiting.
</div>

<div class="row mb-5">
    <div class="col-md-8">
        <p>Our RESTful API provides endpoints for all core and advanced document processing features, allowing you to automate tasks such as PDF merging, image conversion, OCR, and smart data extraction for your custom workflows.</p>
        <h3 class="mt-4">Key Features:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><i class="fas fa-key me-2"></i> Secure API Key authentication</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-hand-paper me-2"></i> Robust rate limiting via token-bucket algorithm</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt me-2"></i> Comprehensive OpenAPI (Swagger) documentation</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-dollar-sign me-2"></i> Flexible pay-per-use billing model</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://example.com/api-docs" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg mt-3 me-2">
            <i class="fas fa-book-open me-2"></i> View API Documentation
        </a>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-lg mt-3">
            <i class="fas fa-user-secret me-2"></i> Generate API Key
        </a>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4 text-center d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center">
        <i class="fas fa-code fa-5x text-muted"></i>
    </div>
</div>

<h2 class="mt-5">Getting Started</h2>
<p>To begin integrating with the FluxDoc API:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Register for a developer account.</li>
    <li>Generate your API Key from your developer dashboard.</li>
    <li>Familiarize yourself with our comprehensive documentation.</li>
    <li>Start making authenticated requests to our processing endpoints!</li>
</ol>
